        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 24 at 7:48PM CDT by NWS Lubbock TX</headline>
        <description>At 748 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Caprock Canyon State Park, moving northeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Silverton, Turkey, Caprock Canyon State Park, Quitaque, Valley
Schools, and South Plains.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
